          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <p><placeName>N<hi rend="underline">o</hi> 9 Reade St N.
                                        Y</placeName>:</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <placeName>Walnut Street</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">Paide</hi>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi>
                                        </add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> Tuesday, 5th
                                        of</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><date>Nisan (April) 1851</date>.</p>
                              <p>May the God of the Universe grant life, etc,<lb/>
                                        <addressee>Rabbi Yitzchek Isaac Leeser</addressee>:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">With an expression of greetings I come<lb/> to beg
                                        of you for an unusual favor.<lb/> A year ago,
                                                  you—<add>?</add> printed Shema Yisreels*<lb/>
                                        written by <persName>Mr. Bernahl</persName>, and
                                                  <persName>Mr. A. Hart</persName><lb/> answered
                                        that the die has been destroyed and<lb/> no more are to be
                                        had, and <del>you</del> I came to<lb/> the conclusion that
                                                  <del>you</del> I ought to make a<lb/> new die,
                                        which <del>you</del> I did, making many<lb/> changes and
                                        improvements in it, so<lb/> that it might agree with the
                                        Divine<lb/> command. But before doing this I asked the<lb/>
                                        lawyer <persName>Joachinson</persName> whether it is
                                        allowed.<lb/> His answer was, "Certainly, since you
                                        made<lb/> and want to make many improvements."<lb/> I then
                                        extended $155., not a cent of mine,<lb/> but money of my
                                        friends who assisted me.</p>
                              <p>*a group of Biblical quotations, usually attached to the<lb/> walls
                                        over the bed of a woman who had just given birth.</p>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <date>4-5-1851</date>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>Now I am told that before selling I<lb/> must inquire more
                                        carefully about the<lb/> laws and customs of this land,
                                        since every<lb/> thing of this sort is prohibited. That
                                        is<lb/> why I hope that you my friend will<lb/> do me this
                                        favor to write to <persName>Mr. Bernahl</persName><lb/> for
                                        permission to reprint the Shima Yisrael<lb/> and sell them.
                                        My view is that you should<lb/> not reveal that they are
                                        already printed<lb/> "but the wise men has eyes in his
                                        head"<lb/> and you may as you please. I do this<lb/> only to
                                        save my life, to be able to<lb/> return the borrowed money,
                                        and not to<lb/> make enemies for myself. But God<lb/> who
                                        knows the hidden things knows that<lb/> the fault lies with
                                                  <persName>Joachinson</persName>. I have<lb/> no
                                        doubt you will do this kindness<lb/> and help me as much as
                                        possible, in order to save my life. God will reward<lb/> you
                                        doubly, etc. etc. Writing with weak<lb/> hands and shaking
                                        knees,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Simeon Cohen
                                                  Nost</persName>, <placeName>9 Reade St. N.
                                                  Y.</placeName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <date>4-5-1851</date>
                              </p>
                    </body>
